# Project Structure Guide

## Directory Organization
- src/ - Main application code
  - agents/ - AI agent implementations (skills, graph agent)
  - tools/ - Reusable utilities (Milvus, Ollama, web search, cache)
  - config/ - Configuration (settings.py, environment variables)
  - mcp/ - Model Context Protocol server implementation

- tests/ - Test suite (mirrors src structure)
  - conftest.py - Shared fixtures and configuration
  - test_*.py - Unit and integration tests

- document_loaders/ - Document loading and embedding utilities
  - core/ - Shared tools (MilvusVectorDB, OllamaClient)
  - local_settings.py - Loader-specific configuration

- chatbots/ - Chat interfaces
  - interactive_chat.py - CLI chatbot
  - react-chatbot/ - Web UI (React)

- docker/ - Docker configuration
  - Dockerfile - Application container
  - docker-compose.yml - Full stack setup

- docs/ - Developer documentation
  - GETTING_STARTED.md - Setup and configuration
  - DEVELOPMENT.md - Code examples and patterns
  - ARCHITECTURE.md - System design
  - API_SERVER.md - REST API documentation

- scripts/ - Utility scripts (moving from root)
  - cache/ - Cache management utilities
  - data/ - Data loading and processing

## File Naming Conventions
- snake_case for Python files and directories
- kebab-case only for Docker/configuration files (.github/actions/)
- UPPERCASE for config files (.env, .gitignore)
- UPPERCASE_WITH_UNDERSCORES for important markdown docs
